## Introduction

In today’s digital age, digital literacy has become an essential skill for students and professionals. It refers to the ability to use digital tools, platforms, and technologies effectively, safely, and responsibly. This project was undertaken as part of the Digital Literacy course to develop practical knowledge and awareness about various digital tools and online practices.

The main objective of this project is to help students understand how to build a professional online presence, communicate effectively using digital platforms, and protect themselves from cyber threats. Through this project, I completed five tasks, each focusing on a specific aspect of digital literacy.

This project has helped me gain hands-on experience with tools like GitHub, LinkedIn, Google Forms, and HackerRank. It also improved my understanding of email etiquette and cyber safety. Overall, this project plays an important role in preparing students for the digital world.

